        "description": "A formal grid convergence study using three systematically refined mesh densities must demonstrate a Grid Convergence Index (GCI) below 2% for construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement. Richardson extrapolation must be documented with observed order of convergence within 10% of theoretical."
      },
      "rationale": "A mesh convergence study was performed using two mesh densities (coarse: ~85k elements; medium: ~210k elements), but a third systematically refined mesh was not generated due to computational resource constraints. The two-mesh GCI estimate for stiffness is 3.8%, exceeding the 2% acceptance criterion. Formal Richardson extrapolation with three meshes and documented observed order of convergence was not completed. Achieved Gradation 2; required Gradation 3. This shortfall is a primary contributor to the Not-accepted decision."
