      },
      "rationale": "Testing was performed at a single ASTM F1717 standard offset distance (44 mm) and a single axial compression angle (0 degrees). No variation in offset distance or load angle was explored to characterize model performance across the clinical loading envelope. Environmental conditions (room temperature, ambient humidity, no lubricant) were documented but represent only one point in the operating envelope. Achieved Gradation 2; required Gradation 3. This shortfall was noted in the original Nagaraja et al. publication as a limitation. This factor shortfall is a contributing factor to the Not-accepted decision."
